<p>Cool! Refresh. Oooh, pretty links. Click the first one. The name is "Octopus66", but
the fun fact and other stuff is <em>still</em> hardcoded. It's time to grow up and finally
make this dynamic!</p>
<h2 id="querying-for-one-genus">Querying for One Genus <a class="headerlink" href="show-404#querying-for-one-genus" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>In the controller, get rid of <code>$funFact</code>. We need to query for a Genus that matches
the <code>$genusName</code>. First, fetch the entity manager with <code>$em = $this-&gt;getDoctrine()-&gt;getManager()</code>:</p>
