<p>Okay team, let's give it a try. Refresh. Looks awesome! The known species is the
number it should be, there is no fun fact, and the JavaScript is still working.</p>
<h2 id="handling-404-s">Handling 404's <a class="headerlink" href="show-404#handling-404-s" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>But what would happen if somebody went to a genus name that <em>did</em> not exist - like
FOOBARFAKENAMEILOVEOCTOPUS? Woh! We get a bad error. This is coming from Twig:</p>
<blockquote><p>Impossible to access an attribute ("name") on a <code>null</code> variable</p>
</blockquote>
<p>because on line 3, <code>genus</code> is null - it's <em>not</em> a Genus object:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="da07c939c3">
